# No Verus ID Creation or Modification

## ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN — No Exceptions

- **NEVER create a Verus ID** (`registernamecommitment`, `registeridentity`, or any variant)
- **NEVER update a Verus ID** (`updateidentity`) directly — all identity updates go through the game nodes only
- **NEVER call `updateidentity` or `update_cmm` manually** via CLI or RPC
- **NEVER reset an identity** (`./bin/bet reset <id>` or `./bin/bet reset_id <id>`)
- **NEVER call `add_dealer`, `register_dealer`, or `deregister_dealer`** without explicit user approval
- **NEVER send funds to or from any Verus ID**

## These Are Real On-Chain Identities With Real Money

The IDs `d1`, `t1`, `p1`, `p2`, `cashier.sg777z.chips.vrsc@`, `dealer.sg777z.chips.vrsc@` exist on the live CHIPS blockchain.
Modifying them has irreversible consequences.

## What This Means in Practice

If any planned action would result in an `updateidentity` transaction being submitted to the chain,
**stop and ask the user first**, even if that action is triggered indirectly by starting a game node.
